html/2605.00146v1/2605.00146v1/x1.png", "score": 10}, {"id": "oai:arXiv.org:2605.00251v1", "title": "Alethia: A Foundational Encoder for Voice Deepfakes", "summary": "Abstract: Existing voice deepfake detection and localization models rely heavily on representations extracted from speech foundation models (SFMs). However, downstream finetuning has now reached a state of diminishing returns. In this paper, we shift the focus to pretraining and propose a novel reci...", "link": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2605.00251", "source": "arXiv Audio & Speech", "image": "https://arxiv.org/html/2605.00251v1/2605.00251v1/fig/pretrain_framework.png", "score": 10}, {"id": "oai:arXiv.org:2605.00022v1", "title": "Putting HUMANS first: Efficient LAM Evaluation with Human Preference Alignment", "summary": "Abstract: The rapid proliferation of large audio models (LAMs) demands efficient approaches for model comparison, yet comprehensive benchmarks are costly. To fill this gap, we investigate whether minimal subsets can reliably evaluate LAMs while reducing costs and data redundancy. Analyzing 10 subset...", "link": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2605.00022", "source": "arXiv NLP", "image": "https://arxiv.org/html/2605.00022v1/2605.00022v1/figures/main.jpg", "score": 9}]}